  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Keep 500 Students Safe at School in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Libuyu Community School is an under-resourced primary school in the rural community of Livingstone, Zambia. In December of last year, we built three new classrooms at the school and dropped their teacher-to-student ratio from 1:80 to 1:45. The next step in improving the learning environment for their students is to build a wall fence around the perimeter of the school&apos;s property. A fence will keep unwanted people and elephants off of the property.</narrative>
  </description>
